avors by staying longer,
even though the paper insisted on adding a quote from <b>Marie-Jos=C3=A9e K=
ravis</b> saying he could have, had he wanted. (Somehow that=E2=80=99s char=
acterized as mutual agreement when Lowry clearly=E2=80=94and smartly=E2=80=
=94decided to take a walk for everyone=E2=80=99s benefit.) <br/><br/>Cue th=
e usual hand-wringing about how hard and complicated these jobs are now. Am=
usingly, only the <i>Times</i> seems to think running a major cultural inst=
itution is a job for someone with =E2=80=9Ca Ph.D. in art history and the a=
bility to hire capable curators.=E2=80=9D Or that it is remotely surprising=
